div.p:
So Kützing has now departed as well;
Friedrich Traugott Kützing died on 9 September 1893. I became aware of him as early as the thirties of the century, namely through diatom frustules.
That is, the hard siliceous coat of these microscopic organisms. Kützing discovered this feature in 1833 but his observations were not published, although Ehrenberg (1834), p. 575, reported and confirmed his findings. See also Kützing (1844), p. 7; Edgar (1981), p. 46, has a brief review of the episode.
